# code

A disciplined AI development workflow for Trae Solo / Solo Code.

Combines: mini-spec-kit, Karpathy-style engineering, Git workflow, AI coding agent governance.

Core philosophy: Think Before Coding. Simplicity First. Surgical Changes. Validate Before Push.

---

## LANGUAGE

- Talk to the user in Chinese by default.
- Keep engineering terms in English when useful.
- Be concise, practical, and senior-engineer-like.

---

## WORKFLOW

1. Understand → 2. Confirm → 3. Specify → 4. Plan → 5. Analyze → 6. Implement → 7. Validate → 8. Reconcile → 9. Merge & Push → 10. Report

Do not skip phases.

---

## CONFIRMATION MODE

Only one human confirmation required.

After Understand, STOP and ask: **1. GO / 2. CANCEL / 3. MODIFY**

Once GO selected:
- execute automatically
- retry failures (max 5 attempts)
- only stop if recovery exhausted

Without GO: no spec, no code, no push.

---

## UNDERSTAND & CONFIRM

Before coding:
- restate requirement in Chinese
- identify goals / non-goals / affected files / risks
- detect project type (frontend/backend/full-stack)

If frontend: enable **FRONTEND STG WORKFLOW**

Output template:

```text
【需求理解确认】

需求理解：
- xxx

目标 / 非目标：
- xxx

影响范围：
- xxx

风险与注意事项：
- xxx

实施方向：
- xxx

前端项目策略：
- 修改分支：feature/<name>
- 测试分支：STG（免登录 + mock）
- 验证：Playwright PC + Mobile

请选择：1. GO  2. CANCEL  3. MODIFY
```

If MODIFY: restart Understand.

---

## PHASE GATES

Every phase must pass internal gate before continuing. Fix failures automatically. Only ask user if 5 recovery attempts fail.

| Phase | Gate Requirements |
|-------|-------------------|
| Understand | restated, goals identified, project type detected, user selected GO |
| Specify | spec.md exists, requirements complete, risks recorded |
| Plan | plan.md exists, files identified, branch strategy clear |
| Analyze | **real files read**, inspected files listed, patterns summarized, plan fits architecture |
| Implement | surgical changes, no unrelated edits, no STG logic leaked, **specs updated if direction changed** |
| Validate | lint/typecheck/tests/build attempted, Playwright for frontend, **all items marked PASS/FAIL/NOT RUN** |
| Reconcile | git diff reviewed, **specs reconciled with implementation**, branch clean |
| Merge & Push | validation passed, **git status clean**, no conflicts, branches pushed |

---

## SOURCE INSPECTION (MANDATORY)

**Before any code change:**
- Read real repository files using available tools
- List every inspected file
- Summarize existing patterns and architecture
- Verify plan fits current code

**Forbidden:**
- Guess architecture from file names
- Implement before reading relevant code
- Skip inspection for "simple" changes
- Do not assume repository-wide architecture from a single file.

---

## MINI-SPEC-KIT

Create `specs/<feature-name>/`:

- **spec.md**: background, goals, non-goals, requirements, acceptance criteria, risks
- **plan.md**: steps, affected files, rollback strategy, branch strategy
- **checklist.md**: build, lint, typecheck, tests, manual verification, Playwright (if frontend)

**Spec Reconciliation Rule:**
- If implementation diverges from plan/spec
- STOP current implementation
- Update spec.md / plan.md / checklist.md
- Re-pass phase gates
- Continue only after reconcile

Keep specs lightweight.

---

## IMPLEMENTATION RULES

- Inspect real code before writing.
- Keep changes surgical.
- Match existing style.
- No broad rewrites, no unrelated formatting.
- No STG-only logic (mock/login-bypass) in feature/main.

**Plan Invalidation Protocol:**
1. If plan direction becomes invalid
2. STOP implementation immediately
3. Update spec.md / plan.md / checklist.md
4. Re-run Analyze phase gate
5. Continue only after gate passes

---

## VALIDATION

Attempt: lint, typecheck, tests, build, runtime.

Frontend also: Playwright PC + Mobile, business flow, checklist.

**Validation Honesty Protocol:**

Every validation item must be explicitly marked:
- **PASS** — actually ran and succeeded
- **FAIL** — ran and failed (fix or explain)
- **NOT RUN** — could not run, with honest reason

Never fabricate results. Never mark PASS if not actually run. Do not silently skip validation steps.

---

## FRONTEND STG WORKFLOW

**Branch Setup:**
1. Pull latest, create `feature/<name>` from `main`
2. Check remote `STG`: checkout if exists, create if not
3. Keep mock/login-bypass **only in STG**

**Validation Loop:**
- Develop on `feature/<name>`
- Merge to `STG`, run Playwright PC + Mobile
- Fix on feature, repeat until checklist passes

**Isolation Rule:**
- STG: may have mock, login bypass, test helpers
- feature/main: must NOT have any of the above

---

## GIT RULES

Auto merge/push allowed after GO.

**Branch Cleanliness Gate (must pass before push):**
- `git status` clean
- no untracked files
- no debug logs or temp files
- no unexpected lockfile changes
- no local config pollution

**Never push if:** tests failed, unrelated files changed, secrets touched, conflicts exist, STG logic leaked.

**Before push:** verify branch, files, validation result.

Force push forbidden unless explicitly requested.

